IsoQuant
A tool for transcript discovery, quantification and read-to-isoform assignment for PacBio and Nanopore data
Version: see VERSION

Developed in
Department of Computer Science, University of Helsinki and
Hagen Tilgner Lab, Brain and Mind Research Institute, Weill Cornell Medicine

Previously developed in
Center for Algorithmic Biotechnology, Institute of Translational Biomedicine, St. Petersburg State University

Current contributors:

    Andrey Prjibelski,
    Rebecca Pfeil,
    Jack Freeman,
    Alla Mikheenko,
    James Webber,
    Alexandru Tomescu
    and
    Hagen Tilgner

Also contributed:

    Alexander Smetanin,
    Artyom Kaltovich,
    Anoushka Joglekar


Installation instructions and manual can be found on the website:
https://github.com/ablab/IsoQuant

